  "prompt": "Is \"Annie\" from Smooth Criminal a real person?",
  "response": "No, \"Annie\" from the song \"Smooth Criminal\" by Michael Jackson is not a real person. The name \"Annie\" originates from the Resusci Anne mannequin used in CPR training. During these training sessions, instructors often ask \"Annie, are you okay?\" to simulate checking if the person is responsive. Michael Jackson was inspired by this scenario for the song, and \"Annie\" functions as a fictional character in the lyrics.",
